{
  "name": "Potion of Poison",
  "type": "consumable",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>This concoction looks, smells, and tastes like a <strong>potion of healing</strong> or other beneficial potion. However, it is actually &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} masked by &amp;Reference[ill]{illusion} magic. An <strong></strong>@UUID[Compendium.world.ddb-lost-mines-phandelver-spells.Item.Vh2b60zHW18RSyFh]{identify} spell reveals its true &amp;Reference[nat]{nature}.</p>\n<p>If you drink it, you take 3d6 &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} damage, and you must succeed on a [[/save con 13 format=long]] or be &amp;Reference[poisoned]{poisoned}. At the start of each of your turns while you are &amp;Reference[poisoned]{poisoned} in this way, you take 3d6 &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} damage. At the end of each of your turns, you can repeat the saving throw. On a successful save, the &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} damage you take on your subsequent turns decreases by 1d6. The &amp;Reference[poison]{poison} ends when the damage decreases to 0.</p>\n</div>",
